# Pomodoro Timer

A simple Pomodoro Timer application built with Python and Tkinter.

![Pomodoro Timer](pomodoro.png)

## Description

This Pomodoro Timer application allows users to set work sessions, short breaks, and long breaks to manage their time effectively. It follows the Pomodoro Technique, a time management method that uses a timer to break down work into intervals, traditionally 25 minutes in length, separated by short breaks.

## Features

- Set custom work session duration
- Set custom short break duration
- Set custom long break duration after a certain number of work sessions
- Visual indication of work and break periods
- Reset timer functionality

## How to Use

1. Clone the repository to your local machine.
2. Ensure you have Python installed.
3. Run the `main.py` file using Python.
4. Use the "Start" button to start the timer.
5. Use the "Reset" button to reset the timer.
6. Enjoy improved time management and productivity!

## Requirements

- Python 3.x
- Tkinter library


